args: This beast is incomprehensible.\n▷Aw, don't take it personally, Laxi.◁
She wants to feed that stray cat, but the\nfurball won't let her near it. What a hoot!
Be silent, Luca. If my target escapes,\nthe fault is yours.
Ha ha! Still, it's unusual to see Laxi\ntake any interest in animals.
I'm as shocked as you are.\nGuess even androids can change.
So, what's up? You need something?
I received a report about the imperial\nsquadron you took captive the other day.
Yeah, I know we've been trying to\npump 'em for intel on the Empire.
They finally agreed to our terms.
This will be a huge help in understanding\nthe situation on the ground in Dyrenell\nafter the recent political unrest.
I wanted to thank all three of you.\nThat was some excellent work.
Aw, it ain't no thing. Hell, we were just\ntrying to figure out more about Eden mode.\nEverything else just sorta...happened.
Plus, I spent half the time as a prisoner.
Affirmative. Luca did nothing. His greatest\ncontribution was remaining unconscious.
▷Ha! So true! Even after we rescued him,\nhe refused to wake up. Laxi had to carry\nhim all the way back to the Halidom!◁
Be really nice if I could deny any of that...
Wait, you brought down an imperial force\nof that size with just the two of you?
And with just one body, too.

Hell, I'd surrender if you sent my entire
stockpile of magical weapons up in smoke
with a single attack. Body count doesn't
matter once you see firepower like that.
Fair enough. Still, it's huge that you've\ngained access to a stable Eden mode\non top of annihilation mode.
Oh, speaking of Eden mode, is that extra\narmor a permanent addition now?
I thought it was something that only\nmaterialized while Eden mode was active.
▷That was the case until recently, but it\nseems to have fully manifested now.◁

With the stabilization of Eden mode,
the mana kiln's condenser resumed
normal function, likely allowing the
regalia to affix fully in place.
Ha! I didn't follow much more than you,\nLuca. This technology is really something.
Laxi and Mascula say the maestro who\nmade them was a peace-loving man, but...
No, I getcha. Why would some peacenik\ngive something THIS much power?

Hostility detected in the target.
Was it an enemy all along?
▷No using daggers on cats, Laxi!◁
Why not? It struck first.
▷It only scratched you because it's\nscared. Now if you don't calm down,\nI'll calm you down myself!◁
How do I rid a target of hostile intent\nwithout causing it fear?
▷Heh. All right, listen up. First, you...◁
I suppose it doesn't matter much.\nWhatever power those two find,\nI'm certain they'll use it wisely.
Interesting. It took the food.\n▷See? If you show someone you don't\nwant to fight, they understand!◁
